-- Russia’s Grain Exports Were 15 Million Tons, Rusagrotrans Says
-- B y   M a r i n a   S y s o y e v a
-- 2011-12-21T14:33:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-21/russia-s-grain-exports-were-15-million-tons-rusagrotrans-says.html
Russia exported more than 15 million
metric tons of grain from July through November, including 12.8
million tons of wheat and 1.7 million tons of barley,
 Rusagrotrans  said.  In November, shipments were almost 2.6 million tons and the
country is expected to export another 2.5 million tons in
December, the country’s biggest carrier of grain by rail said in
a report dated Dec. 15.  Russia’s five biggest grain exporters by volume accounted
for 43 percent of shipments in the first five months of the
marketing season that began July 1, Rusagrotrans said. They were
International Grain Co., a Russian unit of Glencore
International AG, Louis Dreyfus, Yug Rusi, Bunge Ltd. and Aston
FFI, according to the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marina Sysoyeva in Moscow at 
